verses.roman:
iṅhāra ye ei gati, ithe ki vismaya?
tomāra darśana-prabhāva ei-mata haya'

synonyms: iṅhāra—of this Mohammedan governor; ye—which; ei—this; gati—result; ithe—in this; ki—what; vismaya—the wonder; tomāra—of You; darśana-prabhāva—influence of seeing; ei-mata haya—is like this.
translation: "It is no wonder that this Mohammedan governor has attained such results. Simply by seeing You, all this is possible.
